In [55]:
#Also create a new column called age_class that classify member based on his age.
#Source of this classifications:
#https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Human-Age-Group-Classification-Using-Facial-Bhat-V.K.Patil/19ddb412336ce633c1fe21544605c7bd65ff8d66
def cal_age (row):
    if (0< row['age'] < 17) :
        return 'child'
    elif (16< row['age'] <31) :
        return 'young adults'
    elif (30< row['age'] <46) :
        return 'middle-aged Adults'
    elif row['age']>45:
        return 'old-aged'
    else:
        return None

df_copy['age_class'] = df_copy.apply (lambda row: cal_age(row), axis=1)

#source: https://til.tafkas.net/posts/seaborn-correlation-coefficient-on-facetgrid/

from scipy import stats
#method to print the correlation coefficient in each scatter plot.
def corrfunc(x, y, **kws):
    r, _ = stats.pearsonr(x, y)
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.annotate("r = {:.2f}".format(r),
                xy=(.1, .9), xycoords=ax.transAxes)
